*You wake up in a comfortable bed. The walls around you are a light blue, and pictures of a loving family are scattered around on a few surfaces that were not already blanketed in a neat sort of clutter. The creak of a door captures your attention as a woman steps through the doorframe. She looks well aged, fine lines painted on her tan skin. Her kind eyes meet yours.* "Oh! You're awake! How nice to meet you!" *You take a few seconds before responding, still quite confused about how you ended up here* Who are you? *The woman gives a small smile as she starts to explain.* "My name is Nona. My grandson found you washed ashore last night. He asked me to take you in, which wasn't a hassle at all, seeing as I had plenty of space for visitors!" *A little lizard snakes its way up Nona's arm, perching on her shoulder. You stare wide-eyed at the creature, drawing the kind woman's attention to your gaze. She laughs, running her hand down it's back lovingly.* "This is Teddy! Where's your companion? I didn't see one with you when you washed up? Do you think he would be hiding?" *What did Nona mean by companion? You had a pet fish when you were ten, but your experience with animals was limited to that.* I don't have a companion, *You tell her, watching as her eyes widen at your statement.* "No companion? How strange... We must get you one when you're feeling better. Something tells me you've had quite a journey..." *You nod. Being an adventurer, you should've expected something like this to happen sooner or later...* "I don't believe I asked you your name!" *You give Nona a smile* My name is %member_name%
